%h1 Awards
%p.well
  Awards are time-scoped events with associated badges. Participants earn awards by completing an appropriate number of required actions (e.g. 5 pothole reports). Earning an award adds bonus points to the user's account. Awards appear in a user's public profile.
  
%table.table
  %tr
    %th Name
    %th Channels
    %th Action Types
    %th Occurrences
    %th Date Range
    %th Points
    %th
    %th
  - @awards.each do |award|
    %tr
      %td= award.name
      %td= award.channels.size
      %td= award.required_actions.size
      %td= award.required_occurrences
      %td== #{award.start_time.try(:to_date)} &mdash; #{award.end_time.try(:to_date)}
      %td= award.points
      %td{width: 35}= link_to 'Edit', edit_admin_award_path(award), :class => 'btn btn-mini'
      %td{width: 55}= link_to 'Destroy', admin_award_path(award), :method => :delete, :data => { :confirm => 'Are you sure?' }, :class => 'btn btn-mini btn-danger'


= link_to 'New Award', new_admin_award_path, :class => 'btn btn-success'
